---
description: Comment style — explain what, not how; omit when obvious
alwaysApply: true
---

# Comments

All comments in **English**.

## Purpose

A comment names **what a section is for** (role, domain, constraint) so someone new to the file understands it without reading the implementation.

## Do not

- Describe **code flow** (what happens next, step order, “then we…”, “after this…”).
- Narrate **changes** (“formerly…”, “we added…”, “old value was…”).
- Restate what the code already says (`i++ // increment i`).

## When to skip

No comment if the name, structure, or config key is already clear.

## Examples

```yaml
# ❌ Old single-server values were 150 — reduced because we hit OOM
fpm.pool.pm.max_children=20

# ✅ PHP-FPM pool sizing for this site container (see compose mem_limit)
fpm.pool.pm.max_children=20
```

```cfg
# ❌ Do NOT use plain :443 without ssl — that sends HTTP to SSL port
server app app:443 ssl verify none

# ✅ HAProxy → app container over HTTPS; browser TLS ends at HAProxy (certbot)
server app app:443 ssl verify none
```

```php
// ❌ One-off export only — raise if you still hit memory limits
const MIGRATION_MEMORY_LIMIT = '2048M';

// (no comment — constant name is enough)
const MIGRATION_MEMORY_LIMIT = '2048M';
```
